full_description:

# Outline

## Decorators recap (20')

A brief refresher on the structure of a typical decorator (10') plus time for attendees to write a ‚Äúsimple‚Äù decorator (10')

## Classes as decorators (40')

In this section I will establish a parallel between a regular decorator and a decorator written as a class, showing how to map the decorator and the wrapper function to the class's `__init__` and `__call__` methods, as well as establishing a connection between the closure of the function decorator and the data attributes of the class decorator. This will take 15 - 20 minutes. The other 20 - 25 minutes will be spent on exercises.

## Decorators for classes (30')

In this section I will show how decorators for classes typically modify the class in place, for example by plugging in new methods (10'). Then, attendees will have 20' to work on exercises.
